summary: An ordinance vacating a portion of Grant Street (now 9th Avenue South) and other streets and avenues and alleys heretofore platted in the Plan of South Seattle, an addition to the City of Seattle, as recorded in Volume 1 of Plats, page 35, Records of King County, and in the First Addition to South Seattle by J.J. Moss (now a portion of the City of Seattle) as recorded in Volume 1 of Plats, page 53, Records of King County.
